        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-03T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-03T18:00:00-05:00" n="927" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d927">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/10–1345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-03T18:00:00-05:00">December 3, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2442. Urtel 3537, October 13, 10 p.m. With reference to difficulties experienced
                    by Clubb in work at Vladivostok Consulate General please inform Dept whether you
                    consider any useful purpose would be served by continuing to maintain office
                    there or whether any substantial improvement in working conditions at
                    Vladivostok would result from strong representations at Moscow along lines
                    suggested by Clubb.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
